<subSubSection pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="69.[151,1436,1108,1277]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1215,1240]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Notes.</emphasis>
Due to its specialization on 
<taxonomicName box="[617,731,1217,1240]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Vaccinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[617,731,1217,1240]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Vaccinium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this is a potentially valuable pollinator of blueberry. Nests described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Batra" box="[300,442,1252,1276]" firstAuthor="Batra" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="509 - 538" refId="ref83300" refString="Batra, S. W. T. (1980) Ecology, behavior, pheromones, parasites and management of the sympatric vernal bees Colletes inaequalis, C. thoracicus and C. validus. Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 53, 509 - 538." type="journal article" year="1980">Batra (1980)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Rajotte" box="[497,659,1252,1277]" firstAuthor="Rajotte" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="349 - 361" refId="ref99402" refString="Rajotte, E. G. (1979) Nesting, foraging and pheromone response of the bee Colletes validus Cresson and its association with lowbush blueberries. (Hymenoptera: Colletidae) (Ericaceae: Faccinium). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 52, 349 - 361." type="journal article" year="1979">Rajotte (1979)</bibRefCitation>
from Maryland and Connecticut, respectively.
</paragraph>
